One approach to modeling (P, M) is to use some discrete bivariate distribution with certain correlation structure. For example, we can assume (P, M) follows a mixture of bivariate Poisson distributions. Within each mixture component, the correlation between P and (M) is modeled by introducing an additive Poisson component, i.e.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}				\usepackage{amsmath}
